description: Zombies, space babes and WWII fighter pilots! Featuring KID LIGHTSPEED & THE NEUTRON WOMEN Part 1 (of 3)!!
Sci-fi adventure, a wicked western and a sexy alien on the prowl! Featuring KID LIGHTSPEED & THE NEUTRON WOMEN Part 2 (of 3)!!
Surreal origins of life, robo-soldiers and part 3 of KID LIGHTSPEED & THE NEUTRON WOMEN...the comedic conclusion of Chapter 1 of the Kid's story!
Dark arts detectives, a tale of the Monkey King from ancient China and a magical "birth" of sorts!
The latest adventure of KID LIGHTSPEED & THE NEUTRON WOMEN begins! As well as a little boy's completely inappropriate "hero" and a case of the extraterrestrial munchies. Cover by Franchesco!
A superhero in prison, KID LIGHTSPEED's adventure continues and a surreal exploration. Cover by Jason Copland.
A comic book introduction to the world of the DOORKNOB SOCIETY novel, an anthropomorphic noir tale and KID LIGHTSPEED's latest chapter concludes. Cover by Wendell Cavalcanti.
A little western weirdness, some interplanetary existential angst, strange behavior leads to supernatural suspicions, and aliens among us! Cover by Gav Heryng.

A ruthless group of fascists from the Spanish Civil War resurfaces with a series of terrorist massacres. It's up to Jefferson Pritchard and his fellow soldiers, who thought they had destroyed them decades ago, to come out of retirement and put a stop to the fascists' bloody agenda once and for all. Then, ten men representing all the corners of the Warsaw Pact gather to take part in a weekend of hunting and reminiscing. However, their old suspicions and bloody histories constantly hover like unwanted guests. Soon they find themselves in a deadly game of murder and political intrigue.
name: TPB

description:
Shinhye has always dreamed of a life beyond just ordinary school, work and marriage. She daydreams about traveling among the stars. But when aliens kidnap her and bring her aboard their spaceship, she's forced to rethink those dreams. She begins wondering if perhaps it would be better to have her memory erased so she can return to ordinary reality.

The aliens are using Shinhye to capture her new friend Sarah, who they believe is actually the long-lost Princess Seerajeane from their homeworld. Despite the protection of the mysterious Sir REDION, both girls' lives are continually threatened. Shinhye must choose between life on Earth or pursuing adventures in the wider universe - both of which hold their own unique perils...
name: Vol. 2

description: Shinhye continues to deny her destiny as First Princess Seerajeane of Carpion. Despite his duty, her stoic guardian Redion refuses to force her to leave Earth with him. However, dark and alien political forces are at work and psychic assassins lurk in the shadows. When everyone Shinhye holds dear is slain for the sake of getting to her, she resolves upon a terrible revenge on those responsible. Yet, the only road toward attaining that power is for her to brave an alien royal court more treacherous than a viper's nest and become Queen of Carpion.
name: Vol. 3

description: Shinhye loves lying under the night sky with her father, listening to his tales of the constellations, and she dreams of a life among the stars. Little does she know that the stars may come down to her instead. Her journey begins when the Department of Science asks her family to host Sarah, a foreign girl with a unique talent. Unbeknownst to Shinhye, her every dream - and nightmare - is about to come true.
name: Vol. 4

description:
The Thing and She-Hulk team-up to fight against Dragon Man, but later Jen tames him and they fight together against a horde of vampires.

collects:The Thing & She-Hulk: The Long Night #1 and Fantastic Four Annual 2001

Additional note: This is actually #32, the #60 on the cover is a misprint.
name: Das Ding & She-Hulk

description:
Korea's most talked-about series in 2005!

Born into a shaman family, Sunbi has inherited the power to see and communicate with spirits just like her grandmother, a notable shaman and savior of their little fishing village in the South Sea. Early on, she sees things like an imposter shaman being thrashed by a dragon of the deep, and doesn't understand that none of her schoolmates can see such things. Her powers make her the amorous target of hedonistic demons even as a child. Long shielded from the reality of her power, she finally learns the secret of her mother's death, and why her grandmother was never able to leave their village. Enter Sunbi's world in this mind-boggling psychological chiller!

Chapter Titles

  • Prologue: The Unfamiliar Family
  • Chapter 1: The Ritual of the Dragon Spirit
  • Chapter 2: The Dokebi Food
  • Chapter 3: The Departure
name: Vol. 1

description:
With her grandmother gone, Sunbi experiences the twin pains of loss and loneliness. Through frightening and unceasing attacks by the wandering stray demons who find her to be an ideal host, Sunbi discovers just how dangerous this hidden world is, and how much her grandmother had protected her by shielding her from it. There is no one to care for her now. To make matters worse, in the midst of this grief and chaos Sunbi's dead mother visits her as a hideous demon and kills her only friend, Solbang. But just when she thinks she has no one to run to, she encounters a monk who teaches her that the secret of the demons lay in their ability to use her own fears against her. To survive, she must confront her greatest fear and traverse its terrible depths. What is Sunbi most afraid of? Has her grandmother forsaken her? Watch Sunbi as she bravely fights against the sinister dokebis in Volume 2 of her strange world!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 4: A Dark Child
  • Chapter 5: A Dokebi That Walks Out
name: Vol. 2

description:
Now trouble comes at Sunbi from the spirit world and the human world alike! The jealous dokebi, Gwangsoo, visits her at all hours, even calling her his "bride"--but when evil spirits begin to cling to Sunbi, she has no one to turn to but Gwangsoo, who enlists the help of still more dokebis.... So-called real life, meanwhile, is turning out to be just as complicated for our heroine. A chance meeting with the eccentric Professor Kim may reveal help she never expected--and then a mysterious 19-year-old girl visits Sunbi's house, claiming her grandmother's armory as her own. Is the newcomer friend or foe? Find out in the most chilling volume yet of this mind-boggling thriller!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 6: In the Thick of the Forest, Dokebis
name: Vol. 3

description:
One of the most acclaimed manhwa titles in recent years is the fascinating tale of a girl born into a shaman family.

Back Blurb

Trouble comes at Sunbi from the spirit world and the human world alike! The jealous Gwangsoo is driving Sunbi crazy, visiting her at all hours and calling her his "bride" - but when ever more evil spirits begin to cling to her, there's no one else to turn to... So-called real life, meanwhile, is just as complicated. A chance meeting may offer some unexpected help-and then a mysterious girl tries to claim Sunbi's armory as her own. Is the newcomer friend or foe? Find out in the latest volume of this mind-boggling thriller!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 7: Ice Forming
  • Chapter 8: Sprouting
name: Vol. 4
